com.serotonin.bacnet4j.event

Interface DeviceEventListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DeviceEventAdapter, DeviceEventAdapterAsync

    public interface DeviceEventListener
    There are two versions of each method. The "regular" version runs in a worker thread so that client code need not be concerned with completing its processing in any timely manner. The "sync" version runs within the dispatching thread, and so MUST return as quickly as possible. In particular, overrides of the sync methods MUST NOT send requests.
    Author:
    Matthew
